parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear subframe can cause the rear axle to detach from the body of the car, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Squeaking or creaking noise from the rear of the vehicle
jolting action in normal driving conditions
loud grinding noise when accelerating and decelerating
rear differential detaching from the vehicle
subframe cracking or tearing
and the rear axle dropping from the body.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission's reverse gear can cause the vehicle to become stuck, leading to accidents, property damage, and potential harm to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle refuses to go into reverse gear
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting into reverse
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations when attempting to shift into reverse
the vehicle becomes stuck in a gear
the transmission fails to engage any gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to engage gears properly can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck, leading to accidents, property damage, and potential harm to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations when shifting gears
the vehicle becomes stuck in a gear
the transmission fails to engage any gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to vibrate, make loud noises, and potentially lead to loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Loud thumping or knocking noise from the rear of the vehicle
vibration while driving
creaking sound from the front suspension
squeaking noise from the rear while driving
wheels may fall off.
